<dl id="n08048i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08048i">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08048i"> 48(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> official / Sacred Heart</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les &eacute;critures calligraphiques &eacute;tant des esp&egrave;ces d&apos;&eacute;critures syst&eacute;matiques et parfois affect&eacute;es, comme <mark><i>l&apos;&eacute;criture officielle</i> (1) et <i>l&apos;&eacute;criture du Sacr&eacute; Cour</i></mark>, sont des &eacute;critures artificielles. <br><font color="green">[Calligraphic writing is a systematic, and often affected, kind of writing, official writing (1) and the writing of the Sacred Heart are artificial writings.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 277</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
